  "text": "Two million people in the UK had a cancer diagnosis at the end of 2008; some were diagnosed the previous week, whereas others were diagnosed more than 20 years ago ( Figure 1 ; [CITATION_1] . With 309 000 new cases of cancer diagnosed in 2008, the number of people living with cancer is rising every day (Information Services Division (ISD) Scotland, 2010; Northern Ireland Cancer Registry, 2011; Welsh Cancer Intelligence and Surveillance Unit, 2010 ; Office for National Statistics, 2010a) . If current trends continue, there will be 4 million cancer survivors (people living who have had a cancer diagnosis at some point in their lives) by 2030 (estimated, based on [CITATION_2] .",
